The paper deals with reinforcement learning and specifically with the use of options, which are a type of temporal abstraction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for learning with options, which involves casting the problem into a common framework with multi-step off-policy learning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
